				<h3>Immigrants entering the United States through legal channels are highly-educated.</h3>
				<p>While those with a high school education or below made up the vast majority of adult immigrants as recently as 1980, the most common level of education among the recent immigrants we studied was a bachelor’s degree, followed closely by graduate-level education.</p>
