				<h3>Recent immigrants to the United States often arrive with the STEM training U.S. employers need.</h3>
				<p>Employers in recent years have faced a dire shortage of workers with expertise in Science, Technology, Engineering, and Math (or STEM). As recently as 2016, 13 open STEM jobs were posted online for every one unemployed STEM worker. A large number of recent immigrants have degrees in these fields. </p>
