				<h3>Recent immigrants often work in fields with known labor shortages.</h3>
				<p>STEM jobs are not the only ones difficult to fill. In some parts of the country struggle to find enough doctors and nurses to care for the rapidly-aging Baby Boomer population. One NAE study, for instance, found that 135 counties in the United States—often rural ones with large health challenges—lack a single active physician. Researchers also predict the United States will be short more than 900,000 nurses by 2030.</p>
